This paper is about training task-completion dialogue agents using reinforcement learning, which falls under the intersection of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of active learning and human evaluations, which could potentially fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), respectively.
